Russian envoy Victor Possovaluk visited  Jericho on Sunday and praised both Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhak Rabin and  PLO chief Yasser Arafat for the launch of Palestinian self-rule.
Possovaluk, on a Middle East tour as a special envoy of President Boris  Yeltsin, said: "We appreciate the policies of Mr. Rabin's government which has  allowed the Palestinians to take control of Gaza and Jericho.
"It is a chance the Palestinians cannot afford to miss."
The envoy also praised the PLO for its policies and said he "appreciated  the personality" of Arafat.
On Monday, Possovaluk is to meet Rabin and Palestinian leaders in East  Jerusalem.
